    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [175ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop <strong>half</strong> your<strong> Thai basil</strong> finely, including the stalks and keep the<strong> remaining Thai basil leaves </strong>whole</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic </strong>open by squashing it with the side of a knife and remove the skins</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic </strong>and <strong>chopped Thai basil</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and grind to a paste</p><p>Add your <strong>Thai green curry paste </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>fragrant Thai green curry paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>fragrant Thai green curry paste</strong> with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>OnOnce fragrant, add your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>and<strong> lime leaf[ves] </strong>with 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and give everything a mix up until the coconut has dissolved</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mussels</strong> and any juices to the pot and bring to the boil over a high heat (cooking for 4 or more? Use 2 pots!)</p><p>Once boiling, add your <strong>sweet pea pods</strong>, cover with a lid and cook for 5-6 min or until the mussels are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>fragrant Thai green curry mussels</strong></p><p>Tip: Discard any mussels which shells have not opened!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-green-curry-mussels-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>fragrant Thai green curry mussels </strong>with the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>whole Thai basil leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
